Package: kora
Version: __VERSION__
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: __ARCH__
Maintainer: willgcr <hello@willgcr.me>
Depends: libc6, libstdc++6, libcurl4t64 | libcurl4, libsqlite3-0, libncursesw6, libgomp1, libvulkan1
Recommends: mesa-vulkan-drivers | nvidia-driver-libs-vulkan
Suggests: kora-cuda
Homepage: https://wrklabs.org/kora
Description: terminal-based local LLM chat client
 Kora is a terminal-based chat client for local LLMs, built on llama.cpp.
 Includes a three-pane TUI, a multi-model supervisor with an
 OpenAI-compatible HTTP API, SQLite-backed session persistence, and
 markdown rendering.
 .
 GPU acceleration is auto-detected at runtime: this package ships the
 Vulkan backend (works on NVIDIA, AMD, and Intel GPUs with the right
 driver). Install kora-cuda alongside for the CUDA backend on NVIDIA
 hardware. Falls back to CPU when no GPU is available.
